    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 741
                    The Alternate Delegate to the Preparatory Commission of the
                        United Nations (
                        Gerig
                    ) to the Director of the Office of Special
                        Political Affairs (
                        Hiss
                    ) and the Deputy Director of the Office of Special
                        Political Affairs (
                        Ross
                    )Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of Winant.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d741</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">741</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="741" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.<gloss target="#t_CC1">CC</gloss>/7–3145:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 741<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Alternate Delegate to the Preparatory Commission of the
                        United Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GOB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerig</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of the Office of Special
                        Political Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HA2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hiss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Deputy Director of the Office of Special
                        Political Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RJC1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ross</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d741fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">plain</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31">July 31,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7709. <gloss target="#t_Copre1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Copre</hi>
                    </gloss> 4. From <persName corresp="#p_GOB1">Gerig</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_HA2">Hiss</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RJC1">Ross</persName>.</p>
                <p>Regarding officers for <gloss target="#t_ExCom1">ExCom</gloss> (Executive
                    Committee) and <gloss target="#t_PreCo1">PreCo</gloss> (Preparatory Committee)
                    agreement of Soviet awaited on proposal at Potsdam of rotation among five powers
                    in <gloss target="#t_ExCom1">ExCom</gloss> with small or middle-sized powers as
                    officers of <gloss target="#t_PreCo1">PreCo</gloss>.…</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
